SATS reported a small net profit of $4.3 million  a reversal of $109 million loss previous year. The profit included government grants and subsidy of $145 million vs previous year of $272 million. Attributable profit of $20.4 million and MI of negative $16.1 million made up to the $4.3 million profit. EPS is 1.8 cents  and NAV per share is $1.43. No dividend declared.  Share price closed at 4.54. May retreat due to lack of dividend payout. 4.35 will be the first support and if it breaks  may move toward 4.24  4.13 and then 3.98. Strong support is at 3.80.
